                <h2>Planning</h2>
                <p><b>Prep Time:</b> X minutes</p>
                <p><b>Cook Time:</b> 21-23 minutes</p>
                <p><b>Servings:</b> 12 muffins <p>
            </div> 

            <div id="preparation">
                <h2>Preparation</h2>
                <h3>Equipment</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Muffin pan</li>
                    <li>Oven</li>

                    
                </ul>
                <h3>Ingredients</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Whole-grain spelt flour, 1 1/2 cups (195 g)</li>
                    <li>Oat flour, 1 cup (110g)</li>
                    <li>Hemp seeds, 2/3-3/4 cup</li>
                    <li>Cinnamon, 1 1/2 - 2 tsp</li>
                    <li>Sea salt, 1/4 tsp</li>
                    <li>Ground cardamom, 1/4 tsp</li>
                    <li>Baking powder, 2 tsp</li>
                    <li>Baking soda, 1/2 tsp</li>
                    <li>Unsweetened applesauce, 1 cup</li>
                    <li>Plain non-dairy milk, 3/4 cup</li>
                    <li>Maple syrup, 1/4 cup</li>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Original recipe called for 1/2 cup</li>
                    </ul>
                    <li>Vanilla extract, 1 1/2 tsp</li>
                    <li>Raisins, 1/3 cup</li>
                    
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div id="cooking">
                <h2>Cooking</h2>
                <ol>
                    <li>Preheat oven to 350deg</li>
                    <li>In large bowl combine flours, hemp seds, cinnamon, sea salt, and cardamom</li>
                    <li>Sift in the baking powder and baking soda</li>
                    <li>In a medium bowl, combine applesauce, milk, maple syrup, vanilla extract, and raisins - mix all together</li>
                    <li>Fold the wet mixture into the dry mixture, stirring until just combined</li>
                    <li>Put in muffin tin</li>
                    <li>Cook for 21-23 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean</li>
                    
                </ol>

            </div>

            <div id="notes">
                <h2>Notes & Tips</h2>
